# Testing Rules

Default to **JUnit 5 (Jupiter)** (`@Test`, `@BeforeEach`, `@AfterEach` from `org.junit.jupiter.api`) unless the build already standardizes on another framework.

## Test Structure (Arrange-Act-Assert)
```java
@Test
void shouldDoSomethingWhenCondition() {
    // Arrange: set up state
    var entry = new BudgetEntry(...);
    
    // Act: do the thing
    double result = entry.amount();
    
    // Assert: verify
    assertEquals(100.0, result);
}
```

## Test Isolation
- @BeforeEach for fresh setup
- @AfterEach for cleanup
- No shared state between tests
- Mock external dependencies (APIs, files)

## Naming
- `should_<expectation>_when_<condition>`
- Clear, readable names that document intent

## What to Test
- Happy path (normal case)
- Edge cases (empty, null, boundaries)
- Error cases (exceptions, malformed data)
- Integration points (file I/O, API calls)

## What NOT to Test
- Implementation details
- Getters/setters
- Auto-generated code
- Trivial logic that can't break